page: Template:List of great powers by date
message: The original tricolor of Russia was in use long before the second one was created. There is no reason to replace the original flag, because it was used as a merchant flag for a long time before the second flag was introduced as a state flag, and was replaced by the original in 1896. As for the UK and other European powers, whether a state has colonial possessions or not does not define the state’s name. And if it loses its colonial possessions, that does not change its official or common name.
